Definition: a campaign in which the candidate makes speeches but does not travel
Example: William McKinley's dignified front-porch campaign won him the presidency in 1896; her approach was the opposite of a passive front-porch campaign
Synonyms: front-porch_campaign, campaigning, a, campaign, in, which, the, candidate, makes, speeches, but, does, not, travel, William, McKinley, s, dignified, front-porch, won, him, presidency, her, approach, was, opposite, of, passive
Category: noun.act
